provisions for storing personal items in the barracks after graduation for those returning for Summer Session  Summer rooms will be assigned on a first come  first served basis  Those students who have paid for a room and meal plan should report to the Deputy Commandant s Office for room assignment beginning at noon the day before classes begin for each session respectively  After normal business hours you should report to the Barrack s Supervisor in the OC office  At the end of each session you must clear the Barracks in accordance with the procedures outlines in the Commandant s Office  If you desire to stay in Barracks for the long weekend between sessions you must coordinate your stay with the Commandant s Office  You will be assessed an additional fee as the room charge only covers the 5 week session    Register for Summer Courses   Catalogue Summer Session Course Lists Tuition   Fees Important Dates  Canceled Courses Courses Subject to Cancellation Attendance   Refund Policies  Summer Forms Barracks Check In Staff Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI  Teresa Evans Administrative Assistant 303 Shell Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7213 F   540  464 7726 E evanstl vmi edu  Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI  Teresa Evans Administrative Assistant 303 Shell Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7213 F   540  464 7726 E evanstl vmi edu Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI Academics Home Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Session Summer Transition Program Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI Undergraduate Research  SURI Teresa Evans Administrative Assistant 303 Shell Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540